📁 Dataset Description

The dataset used in this project is obtained from The Cancer Imaging Archive (TCIA) — a publicly available and widely recognized repository for medical imaging research.

For this project, we utilize a breast MRI dataset that contains real MRI scans of breast cancer patients.

⸻

1️⃣ Type of Data

• Breast MRI scans
• Provided as 2D slices or 3D volumes depending on the collection
• Images are stored in medical imaging formats such as DICOM 
• Each scan corresponds to a real patient but is fully anonymized

⸻

2️⃣ Labels

Each patient scan is associated with a recurrence label:

• 0 → No recurrence
• 1 → Recurrence

Label information is extracted from the metadata file provided with the dataset.

⸻

3️⃣ Dataset Components

The dataset consists of:

• Raw MRI images
• A metadata file containing:
 • Patient ID
 • Recurrence label
 • Additional clinical notes (not used in this project)

⸻

4️⃣ Why This Dataset Was Selected

This dataset was chosen because:

• It is publicly available and ethically safe
• It contains real clinical MRI scans
• It is widely used in academic research
• It supports reproducibility of results
• It does not require institutional approval

⸻

5️⃣ Usage in This Project

In this project, the dataset is used to:

• Preprocess MRI images (cleaning, normalization, resizing)
• Convert medical image formats into model-ready inputs
• Create training, validation, and testing splits
• Train a CNN to learn recurrence-related patterns
• Evaluate model performance

⸻

6️⃣ Ethical & Privacy Considerations

• All images are anonymized by TCIA
• No personal identifiers are included
• No private hospital data is used
• The project complies with ethical research standards